      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Every Scrabble player has wondered: what's the absolute maximum you could score in a single turn? The answer is OXYPHENBUTAZONE — a 15-letter anti-inflammatory drug name that, when played across two triple-word squares with perfect crossing words, theoretically scores 1,778 points. It'll never happen in a real game, but the math is fascinating.</p>

